<br>
&quot;Congratulations Fair-faced Aphrodite. The Goddess of all things fair and beautiful has proven her worth to all those upon the hilly cap of Olympus. Do take the fruits of your victory, and celebrate. For this joyous day will go down in the record books!&quot; Apollo smiled to Aphrodite, as he heard the harsh words of Hera to Paris.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh Hera, don't get your toga in a twist. No one wants to hear it. Go and take your rage somewhere else, for this is a time to celebrate. Not only the union of Peleus and Thetis, but of the victory of one of your fellow goddesses! You should be ashamed of yourself, acting like such a child! Now bite your tongue, and congratulate Aphrodite like a gracious loser. Your lose is far from the fault of Paris. So Hera, do calm down and enjoy the rest of the wedding. Do not make it a miserable time for the rest of us, because you don't know how to back down gracefully.&quot; Apollo's face looked hurt, how had Hera taken out her anger on Paris, a mortal who had known no better of his choices. He had not cared what type of punishment Hera would try and cast upon him. He would not allow her to victimize Paris, or ruin the party for anyone else.<br>
<br>
He walked to young Paris and smiled down at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do not take Hera's words to heart, young Paris. She speaks out of rage.&quot; Apollo looked coldly back at Hera.<br>
<br>
&quot;And do not fright. She will bring  you no misfortune, for I will not allow it. As will not the other gods upon Olympus. We watch over you always, and shall not let Hera release her dreadful rage upon you. For you have done nothing on this day but make a decision that you thought was right. For Hera does not understand, that perhaps it was another who judged, maybe she would have won. But it is not another, tis you Paris who chose on this day. And tis you who will receive the rewards and the repercussions of your choice.&quot; Apollo smiled to him, turning around and raising his hands in celebration. <br>
<br>
There was still much party to revel in.<br>
